Subject: Re: [T2] J-tubes for Late bays-Do they exist???

>Is there an equivalent of these J-tubes for pancake motors??

Aftermarket? NO

But, the VW 411\412 heater boxes are the best  J-tube going. Just find
yourself an old set of boxes, remove the tin and BAM, you have j-tubes that
need no modification and will bolt to the '74 style exhaust.

http://www.germansupply.com/worktruck/jtube1.jpg

But, you will need to fab a couple tabs for tin and such...

Collie
www.germansupply.com
